    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-02-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-02-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="243" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d243">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Pruyn</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 9.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States in
                                        Japan,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Kanagazva,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-02-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 13, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to inform you that I have
                            received a letter from the ministers for foreign affairs, in which they
                            state that they had determined not to send the embassy to the treaty
                            powers, as previously announced.</p>
                <p>In my despatch, No. 57, of the 3d September last, I informed you that the
                            embassy would not go further than Shanghai, the appointment having been
                            made only for the purpose of gaining time, by inducing the hostile party
                            to believe that the Tycoon had not abandoned the hope of obtaining from
                            the treaty powers the concession of the closing of this port.</p>
                <p>The letter of the ministers for foreign affairs is only of importance as
                            another evidence of the increased strength of the government.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, sir, very respectfully, your most obedient
                            servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>ROBERT H. PRUYN, <hi rend="italic">Minister Resident in
                                    Japan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, Washington.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
